01/11/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis met with his Serbian counterpart, Vojislav Kostunica, on Monday (31 October). 
Afterwards, he said a solution to Kosovo's status must not be imposed, but rather must result from substantial negotiations. 
Karamanlis also stressed the importance of fully implementing the internationally set standards for Kosovo, especially enhancement of minority rights. 
Kostunica is on a two-day formal visit to Greece.
In related news, Serbian media are reporting that UN Secretary General Kofi Annan has submitted a letter to the UN Security Council, officially proposing the appointment of former Finnish President Maarti Ahtisaari as UN special envoy in the Kosovo talks. 
(ANA, MPA, Beta, RTS, Tanjug - 31/10/05)
